		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I got this link from a friend, acording to him it is the best of all the online translation services he tried (including google and babelfish)
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.ocn.ne.jp/translation/">http://www.ocn.ne.jp/translation/</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />it's alittle hard to understand it first as it is in japanese <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" />
<br />but for url.. type in url in the textbox with the url text next to it and then select the 2nd radiobox from left and push the button
<br />
<br />for text it's almoast the same but you fill in the text in the other textbox a bit down the page and select the 2nd radiobox from the left under this textbox and push the button under this textbox.
<br />
<br />I hope I explained it somewhat ok. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" />
<br />
<br />edit. ops. you want it the other way aorund.. english to japanese.
<br />then select the radiobox furthest to the left
<br />
<br />edit2..
<br />to help you even more the radioboxes are (from left to right)
<br />eng2jpn | jpn2eng | kor2jpn | jpn2kor | chi2jpn | jpn2chi

		

		</td>
	</tr>
